entries.femaleVariant: Combat mode auto-initiates when a threat is present, and, uh... there's no way to stop it.
Learned how the behavioral chip works at Clouds.
And that's it?
Always seemed like they must be pretty easy to modify. I'm surprised I didn't get the idea the moment we walked into Maiko's office.
Finally, someone said it.
Pulled that sequence from a kung fu training virtu.
How did you ever come up with this?
entries.maleVariant: How'd you ever come up with this?

entries.femaleVariant: Tech that's all pros and no cons – I don't buy it. Side effects, spill 'em.
entries.maleVariant: Tech that's all pros and no cons? I don't buy it. Side effects, spill 'em.

entries.femaleVariant: Can't find a workaround.
I dunno. Only way to determine that'd be through months of testing on a range of subjects.
All right... gotta see it to believe it.
You wanna help – I get that. But I'm more'n happy to pay your fee in full.
Speakin' of gratitude… stuff I'm askin' you to do, well – usually comes with a price tag, I know.
Hooo, shit… I'm scared, V.
I'd like to hear the answer to that, too.
The body'll react as if executing a well-trained series of movements.
Chip's impulses supplant any natural reflexes, so it'll make users feel like they're experiencing cyberpsychosis.
Already tested it out on Tom.
[Stand] Not bad.
Gotta admit – not bad.
Yeah, for the market square in Kabuki. Nah, before we start talkin' serious biz, gonna need to see serious action.
You just saw him…
I'm all outta questions.
OK… prolly settles it – the chip works.
entries.maleVariant: OK, OK… That prolly settles it – the chip works.

entries.femaleVariant: Where do we find him?
Who's Hiromi Sato?
Where do we find this Hiromi?
Hiromi Sato? Who's that?
Clouds' real boss. He rarely shows, but you can't so much as sneeze without him finding out.
At his apartment, H8 megatower. Topmost floor, it's a penthouse. Almost never steps outside its glass walls.
Maiko, hold up. Give us a lift?
Only if you don't talk to me. I feel a migraine coming on.
[Stand] Better be goin'.
Got an expert in causing bodily harm among us. I wanna see how Tommy handles her.
entries.maleVariant: Got an expert in causing bodily harm among us. I wanna see how Tommy handles him.

entries.femaleVariant: So how about it? V? Tom? Roxie? Made up your minds?
You can count on me.
Sorry, not for me. Gotta manage on your own.
Count me in, Judy. Already said I'd help, didn't I?
entries.maleVariant: Count me in, Judy. I already said I'd help, didn't I?

entries.femaleVariant: Nah, not up for this. Got no skin in the game, think you'll do fine without me.
entries.maleVariant: No, not up for this. I got no skin in the game, think you'll do fine without me.

entries.femaleVariant: Thanks, V.
Save the gratitude for later, please.
Come on, V… No point even tryin' without you.
[Stand] Got other things on my mind.
Feels like it's only right.
Out of the question.
Much appreciated.
Judyyy! For real? No, don't wanna hear it.
entries.maleVariant: Judy... for real? No, don't wanna hear it.

entries.femaleVariant: All right... thanks. Nice of you to think of that.
It's late, you're tired.
You can crash on my couch if you want.
Um… V, everything OK?
Aaaargghh….
Forget about it. It's passed.
Yeah, likely the Relic's doing.
Relic's killing me.
It's passed. Forget about it.
Yeah, likely the Relic. And Johnny fucking Silverhand.
Remember the heist Evelyn hired us for, the Relic I was gonna klep?
entries.maleVariant: 'Member the heist Evelyn hired us for, the Relic I was gonna klep?

entries.femaleVariant: Is it the Relic, damaged biochip you told me about? Silverhand's engram?
What the hell, V? You, like, sick?
Rather not kill anyone.
Rather not have to flatline anyone.
Hope is it won't be necessary.
Overpower Hiromi, humiliate him – should be enough. Bosses'll put him outta the game.
Plan could just work.
Better off trying to get at him on the street.
It'll be a show of strength.
Hm, plan just might work.
entries.maleVariant: Hm, yeah, plan just might work.

entries.femaleVariant: Maiko – take it you're on board, too?
entries.maleVariant: Maiko – I take it you're on board, too?

entries.femaleVariant: Wouldn't be wasting my time here if I wasn't.
Wouldn't it be better to ambush him on the street, like, while he's chomping on a scopdog or takin' a piss in a back alley?
Hiromi don't go anywhere without security, so one – makes no difference. Two – this is only a show of force, demonstrating what we are capable of.
Why even try breakin' into a penthouse? Probably crawlin' with guards.
entries.maleVariant: Why even try breakin' into a penthouse? It's probably crawlin' with guards.

entries.femaleVariant: This just might work.
If we get him in his apartment, where he thinks he's completely safe, bosses'll understand what we're lookin' to demonstrate.
My, my. There's a flickering in that skull sponge of yours, after all.
Solo skills don't lie in just executing movements.
There are split-second processes that happen – logistics, decision-making. Result of years of practice.
entries.maleVariant: There's split-second processes that happen – logistics, decision-making. Result of years of practice.

entries.femaleVariant: Hey, V. Come on in.
Hey. Tom Caldera. You must be V?
Nice to meetcha.
Everyone here?
Hey, Tom. Pleasure to meetcha.
Same. Come on.
Everyone here already?
Yup. You're the last.
Come on in.
Pizza's getting cold.
We're in the kitchen.
You made it, good. Grab a seat.
Changed your mind, after all?
Subtle as always.
So, changed your mind, huh? Quickly, too.
I'm here. Doubt I need to explain why.
Subtlety comes naturally to you, doe'n't it?
Yeah, odd. Given how much work I gotta put into it.
Fine. Rather not argue.
Actually, you do need to explain.
All right, chill. Not here to squabble with you.
entries.maleVariant: All right, chill. I'm not here to squabble with ya.

entries.femaleVariant: Wouldn't put it past you.
Judy convinced you. Call me satisfied.
Now, here's the thing – gonna insist you explain. If we're to pull this off, I need to be sure you're all in and know why you're all in.
entries.maleVariant: Here's the thing – gonna insist you explain. If we're to pull this off, I need to be sure you're all in and know why you're all in.

entries.femaleVariant: You don't know the first thing about Clouds, do you? Hiromi Sato and the other Tyger Claw bosses see and hear everything that goes on there.
I didn't get this far by shouting all my plans from the window.
Done saying hello to each other?
Revolution won't plan itself...
How are ya?
You work at Clouds, too?
How are ya?
OK, I guess, but... y'know, sad as hell.
You work at Clouds too?
Better than waitin' on suits… Dream was to go into showbiz, though.
This is Roxanne. She's worked at Clouds longer than any of us.
Hello.
Did you know Evelyn well?
Itching for revenge?
Feeling any better?
[Sit] Nice to meetcha.
[Sit] Congrats on lasting that long.
Hey. Nice to meetcha.
When I heard what you pulled at Clouds... Shit, I so regretted I was off that day.
Heh, respect. A feat in itself from what I've seen of the place.
entries.maleVariant: Huh, yeah, respect. A feat in itself from what I've seen of the place.

entries.femaleVariant: Just been lucky, I guess.
Feelin' better? You look better.
I'm on autopilot – I don't think, just do.
Sound method.
So what's this plan all about?
entries.maleVariant: So, what's this plan all about?

entries.femaleVariant: Were you and Evelyn close?
Yeah… Blew up in her face when she showed up back at Clouds. She was supposed to be long gone, the one who got away.
But deep in my heart, I was glad to see her back.
Feel like such a gonk now…
Come here 'cause you want payback for what happened to 'er?
That's for sure…
But I just wanna have a normal job, too. No fears, no tears, y'know?
You'll never get rid of the stench of the corpse…
Mind steppin' outside? Can't smoke in here.
You'll air it out later.
I modified the behavioral chip. It can equip any doll with a motor reflex system… In other words, make the doll move and fight like a preem-tier solo.
Fascinating, isn't it? What one can learn while tuning fake orgasms for the Moxes.
But it's basically the same as when we activate ourselves for a client.
Need to see it to believe it.
This have any side effects?
How'd you ever come up with this?
Being a solo's lots more than executing a series of movements.
There's an ethical side, too… You could murder someone and not remember a thing.
Doubt your chip's capable of compensating for that.
You're prolly right… but I don't see another way. Alternative's intensive training, but we don't have time for that.
Tom?
Count yourself lucky, what with all the cams and mics in Clouds…
Tyger Claws would sooner dig those chips outta the dolls with screwdrivers than let an idea like this run its course.
[Stand] Unconvincing.
V?
Nm-mm, not convinced. If I'm gonna count on ninja-dolls, gonna need to see some real action.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, not convinced. If I'm to count on ninja-dolls, I'm gonna need to see some real action.

entries.femaleVariant: I saw a bar trick. I wanna see a fight.
Like, wanna spar?
What else?
Just don't mess up my digs, OK? I like it here.
Hehh... happy now?
I'm rarely happy. But that was proof enough.
Let's get to it, then. You’ve got an elite force of three muscleheads and a techie.
What now?
Guards and Tyger Claws in and around we'll overpower – take down, disarm, escort 'em out. Clouds'll be ours.
Bosses we'll give an ultimatum – a cut of the proceeds in exchange for never showin' their faces at the club again.
And havin' no say in how the club's managed.
Taking out the security there won't solve anything. Claws'll just send more. Hiromi Sato's the man you gotta get to.
Claws trust him, respect his opinion… he is one of them. We can try to convince him, but... it's doubtful. We stand a better chance by injecting him with a dose of fear.
But I'll figure out a way to get us inside.
Nice work, Judy. Outdid yourself.
If you were to sell that... Be the richest Judy in the NUSA.
entries.maleVariant: If you were to sell that, heh... You'd be the richest Judy in the NUSA.

entries.femaleVariant: Please. Plenty o' killin' machines in the world. I don't wanna turn more people into 'em.
After this, chips're gettin' micronuked.
Which is a lot more than street thuggery.
Will Tom and Roxanne come?
Tom and Roxanne gonna come with?
No. Whole point's to strike both places at the same time. They'll take care of business at Clouds.
Two-pronged assault… Lovin' it.
That's what I thought… A half-baked, insane plan. You can't see more than an inch ahead of you.
What she said.
entries.maleVariant: What he said.

entries.femaleVariant: Sorry, Jude. Got other things on my mind.
entries.maleVariant: I'm sorry, Jude. I got other things on my mind.

entries.femaleVariant: 'K. Don't make excuses.
Sheesh, why'd you even show? Of all the wasted evenings I've had in my life, this one comes in a solid third.
Well then. That's all she wrote.
I'll set up the meet with Hiromi and let you know. I need a couple days.
Have fun. Toodle-loo!
I… I need to think about it. Never wasted anyone before, y'know.
I'm with it all the way.
V?
But--
Eh-eh-eh! Not a word.
entries.maleVariant: Ep-ep-ep! Not a word.

entries.femaleVariant: Ah, don't mention it.
V? You don't look so hot…
Ughhh… OK… OK, I'm better, fine.
entries.maleVariant: Ughhh… OK… OK, I'm better, I'm fine.

entries.femaleVariant: Is it worse?
Knew it could only get worse.
But you do know how to get rid of him, right?
Yeah. Workin' on it.
If there's anything I can do… and I mean anything. All you gotta do's holler.
[Lean] Sure, thanks.
Best be goin'.
Sounds great, thanks.
Suit yourself.
I'll holo you once Maiko's set up the meet with Hiromi.
Ugh, couldn't forget that in a million years.
That biochip… well, long story short, it had Johnny Silverhand's mind on it. An engram of it that's overwriting my mind.
You bein' serious?
Truly wish I wasn't.
Fuck… Anything at all you can do?
One can hope.
Don't worry 'bout it. Make yourself at home.
So, what's the plan.
So then, what's the plan?
Need to wait for Maiko.
Come on, don't be a wuss.
Hahaha! Look at me go! Ya see that?!
It's on now!
Whoo! Heh, gotta do some cardio.
Happy now?
You drop a lot of 'em, don't you? What's your secret?
Fine, I'll sit by the window.
I'm all right now.
So what's the plan?
Nice work, Judy.
By the way… Forrest is doing fine.
By the way… Forrest didn't show up for work today. Or yesterday.
Should be happy as his boss.
Prolly sick or skipped town.
That so? Well, you're his boss... so guess that should make you happy.
entries.maleVariant: Is that so? Well, you're his boss, so – guess that should make you happy.

entries.femaleVariant: Got sick, maybe. Or hit the lottery jackpot, bought himself a ticket to the Moon.
entries.maleVariant: Ah, got sick, maybe. Or hit the lottery jackpot, bought himself a ticket to the Moon.

entries.femaleVariant: He's not comin' back. Doubt I need to explain why to you.
entries.maleVariant: He's not coming back. Doubt I need to explain why to you.

entries.femaleVariant: Don't intend to end 'im. Not now, not never.
He ain't comin' back. Doubt I need to explain why.
Don't intend to kill him.
Hmm. Could be anything.
Me? I've got no idea why. Remember that.
What you're saying is, he'll remain in good health?
Yes.
I have no idea what you're talking about. And I advise you to remember that.
[Stand]
Just eat the free pizza and then we're outta here, OK?
No shit, I wonder why...
If you've got something to say, just say it.
entries.maleVariant: If you got something to say, just say it.

entries.femaleVariant: Got any complaints?
Who – me? This is my impressed face.
Don't tell me you're seriously considering this? Stickin' our precious necks out for a bunch of whores?
[Sit]
Don' worry your head about it. Not like you can hurt him.
Congrats on lasting that long.
Nice to meetcha.
Everything chill? You OK?
